Admin_guidePanel_Earth_p: Earth scene helps user to learn about the global asset information. The asset granularity on earth is to park, showing the geography information, basic information and thumbnail of the park, to facilitate the user's macro presentation.
Admin_guidePanel_Earth_p1: Earth scene editor provides the following functions:
Admin_guidePanel_Earth_p2: 1. To replace the image of the skybox, sun and earth
Admin_guidePanel_Earth_p3: 2. Double click to add a park on the earth, and set the relevant information of the park.
Admin_guidePanel_Earth_p4: 3. In move mode, select and drag the park, and save the park location.
Admin_guidePanel_Setting_earth: Configure the display effect of the earth
Admin_guidePanel_Park_p_3: 3. Double click building to set the floors
Admin_guidePanel_Building_p: Double click building in park scene to set the floors, or set the floors here
Admin_guidePanel_Floor_p_1: Building is added in park scene, and it may be a single floor or multi-floor. The building management and modeling take the floor as a unit.
Admin_guidePanel_Floor_p_2: Scene editor is used to facilitate floor modeling, it supports to import dxf file or create the room by dragging, also supports to load the saved floor for re-editing. Area can be added to separate the room logically.
Admin_guidePanel_Floor_p_3: The scene editor can save data for asset and asset model. When the floor is saved as an asset object, you can set the building to which it belongs and its location (floor height)
Admin_guidePanel_Floor_p1: Scene editor provides the following functions:
Admin_guidePanel_Floor_p2: 1. To create the room type for all floors, including inner wall, outer wall, column, door, window and glass wall by importing or drawing
Admin_guidePanel_Floor_p3: 2. To import or draw channel, rack and device
Admin_guidePanel_Floor_p4: 3. To import or draw camera, smoke detector, temperature point, humidity point and leakage line
Admin_guidePanel_Floor_p5: 4. To import or draw air conditioning, power distribution cabinet, battery pack, fire extinguisher and generator set
Admin_guidePanel_Floor_p6: 5. To import or draw office furniture, computer and plant
Admin_guidePanel_Setting_rack: Model editor is provided to edit rack model. The rack can also be added by dragging in scene editor or importing Excel
Admin_guidePanel_Module_edit_p_1: Although the system provides a variety of rack models, there are still users need to customize their own racks,
Admin_guidePanel_Module_edit_p_2: Model editor is provided to facilitate users to customize rack model. Users can create a brand new rack or modify the existing rack based on requirements.
Admin_guidePanel_Module_edit_p_3: In model editor, select a model and modify its properties in the property sheet on the right.
Admin_guidePanel_p_1: In scene editor, the rack can be added by dragging, but need to drag or copy one by one. When the rack amount is large, it's quite boring.
Admin_guidePanel_p_2: In order to identify the ownership of rack, create a floor or load the existing floor first before adding racks in scene editor. For example, dragging a rack
Admin_guidePanel_p_3: to a floor, the rack belongs to this floor, and its location is relative to this floor. In actual situation, there are room and channel.
Admin_guidePanel_p_4: In order to meet business needs, add room or area to the floor, and add channel in the room or area (room or area and channel can be added when creating the floor, not listed separately here)
Admin_guidePanel_p_5: When dragging in the editor, the objects created by dragging belong to the object where the mouse is located on, suitable for area, channnel and rack.
Admin_guidePanel_Create_rack_in_editor: Create rack in editor (a floor must be selected in previous step before editting)
Admin_guidePanel_Excel_import_p: When the data amount is large, import racks by Excel is much more convenient. On the Import Tab, download the Excel template first, prepare data according to the rules of the template, and then import the data.
Admin_guidePanel_Device_p: Model editor is provided to facilitate the device model creation. Device can be added by importing Excel.
Admin_guidePanel_Model_p_1: Although the system has provided a variety of device models, users may still need to customize their own device,
Admin_guidePanel_Excel_p_2: Model editor is provided to facilitate users to customize device model. Users can create a brand new device or modify the existing device based on requirements.
Admin_guidePanel_Excel_p_3: In model editor, select a model and modify its properties in the property sheet on the right.
Admin_guidePanel_Excel_import_device_p: 'Import device by Excel, on the Import Tab, download the Excel template first, prepare data according to the rules of the template, and then import the data.'
Admin_guidePanel_Panel_p: In the panel editor, there are a variety of components including different types of interfaces, ports and indicators for users to customize their panels.
Admin_guidePanel_Panel_p2: 1. Load the device which needs to set the panel
Admin_guidePanel_Panel_p3: 2. Drag the panel style from the panel back
Admin_guidePanel_Panel_p4: 3. Drag panel components and arrange them
Admin_guidePanel_Link_p: The system provides the link list management, i.e. CURD of link. The link can be added by Excel import.
Admin_guidePanel_Excel_import_link_p: Import link by Excel, after entering the link, download the Excel template first, prepare data according to the rules of the template, and then import the data.
